definitions.definition: A Scottish habitational surname . from a place in Dumfriesshire , meaning "John's town".
An English surname, variant of Johnson .
A village and community in Pembrokeshire , Wales ( OS grid ref SM9310 ) .
A suburb of Palmerston , Northern Territory , Australia .
A city in Polk County , Iowa , United States .
An unincorporated community in Franklin County , Pennsylvania , United States .
A town in Providence County , Rhode Island , United States .
A town in Edgefield County , South Carolina , United States .
